HELP SYSTRMDEV                                      A.Sloman August 1988

    systrmdev(<device record>) -> <boolean>;

SYSTRMDEV is a test for whether a device record refers to a terminal. It
returns TRUE if the device is a terminal, and FALSE otherwise.

For more information on Input/Output procedures, see
REF *SYSIO
REF *SYSUTIL
REF *CHARIO

HELP * INPUT
HELP * OUTPUT

